default&#xa0;default3.1.
default&#xa0; 
defaultThe CAA oversight regime covers flight operations and flying training, aircraft maintenance, aerodromes
default and air traffic control.  Specialists also cover dangerous goods and cabin safety aspects.  Condition and suitability of helicopter landing deck areas on offshore installations are overseen by the independent Helideck Certification Agency, which is audite
defaultd by CAA specialists.
default&#xa0;
default3.2.
default&#xa0; 
defaultAudits and inspections take place on a rolling schedule at each company headquarters and at all operating bases against specific requirements informed by best practice judgement.  The subsequent schedule is determined against previou
defaults company performance, and the CAA will vary oversight accordingly.  Many aspects, including management arrangements, company procedures, training and records are assessed and flight checks take place on public transport flights.  
defaultThe CAA maintain a c
defaultlose 
defaultliaison is with each operator between formal visits, and regular meetings occur.  
defaultCAA inspectors
default are qual
defaultified and experienced personnel
default, trained in 
defaultauditing techniques and, in the case of flight operations assessments, qualified pilots fly on selected fli
defaultghts to ensure safe practices and that company procedures are being followed.
